 is forced to implement  and , even though it doesn’t need them. must have a  method, but boats don’t drive on roads. is also required to implement irrelevant methods.If an interface forces a class to implement unnecessary methods, the code becomes fragile: any change to the interface will affect , even if they don’t use the new methods.The code is harder to read: a developer seeing  might wonder if a car can actually sail, reducing code predictability.If we later add a , , or , we will have to modify the interface again.We separate interfaces into distinct responsibilities.protocol Drivable {
    func drive()
